    "vulnerability": "A02: Cryptographic Failures - SSL Certificate Mismatch",
    "description": "The application uses a self-signed certificate issued to an internal hostname (misp.local), which does not match the public domain (misp-agency.mof.go.th). This creates a Man-in-the-Middle (MitM) risk.",
    "severity": "Medium",
    "evidence": {
      "command": "echo | openssl s_client -connect 124.109.24.61:443 -servername misp-agency.mof.go.th 2>/dev/null | openssl x509 -noout -subject",
      "output": "subject=C=LU, ST=Luxembourg, L=Luxembourg, O=MISP, OU=MISP, CN=misp.local, emailAddress=misp@misp.local"
    }
  },
  {
    "vulnerability": "A05: Security Misconfiguration - Server Version Disclosure",
    "description": "The Server HTTP header explicitly leaks the web server version and operating system, which can aid attackers in finding specific exploits.",
    "severity": "Low",
    "evidence": {
      "request": "GET / HTTP/1.1\nHost: misp-agency.mof.go.th\nAccept: */*\n",
      "response": "HTTP/1.1 302 Found\nDate: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 10:07:23 GMT\nServer: Apache/2.4.58 (Ubuntu)\nSet-Cookie: MISP-aa742f1e-f5bf-4835-928b-9af1018c2381=l0djunadle9ceu6no8no3t3hn6tkegd3; expires=Sat, 25 Apr 2026 22:07:23 GMT; Max-Age=216000; path=/; secure; HttpOnly; SameSite=Lax\nExpires: Mon, 26 Jul 1997 05:00:00 GMT\nLast-Modified: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 10:07:23 GMT\nCache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, post-check=0, pre-check=0\nContent-Security-Policy: default-src 'self' data: 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; object-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; worker-src 'none'; child-src 'none'; frame-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; form-action 'self'; connect-src 'self'; manifest-src 'none'; report-uri /servers/cspReport; upgrade-insecure-requests\nX-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block\nLocation: https://misp-agency.mof.go.th/users/login\nX-Content-Type-Options: nosniff\nX-Frame-Options: DENY\nContent-Length: 0\nContent-Type: text/html; charset=UTF-8"
